---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
import PageMeta from '../../components/PageMeta.astro';
import PageFooter from '../../components/PageFooter.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Transcripts index"
  description="Every transcript on file — videos, all-member updates, DPMSG sessions."
  page="transcripts"
>
<PageMeta category="Engagement" variant="brand" updated="Updated 2026-05-14" />

      <h1>Transcripts index</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Every transcribed session in the archive — public video transcripts, Sandbox
        monthly updates, DPMSG Trust &amp; Interoperability Steering Group sessions.
        Useful for full-text search and for AI summarisation against the corpus.
      </p>

      <h2 id="videos">Public videos</h2>
      <p>15 OPDA YouTube transcripts + 1 Vimeo (Smart Data Challenge prize). Full catalogue at <a href="43-video-library.html">Video library</a>.</p>

      <p>Location: <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/05-engagement/videos-youtube/transcripts/"><code>source/05-engagement/videos-youtube/transcripts/</code></a> · embedded video transcripts (Vimeo &amp; auto-detected YouTube): <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/05-engagement/videos-youtube/embedded/"><code>source/05-engagement/videos-youtube/embedded/</code></a></p>

      <h2 id="sandboxUpdates">OPDA Sandbox monthly all-member updates</h2>
      <p>Four transcribed sessions covering Feb – May 2026. Each is the project status briefing OPDA gives its members at the start of each month.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>February 2026</strong> — <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/engagement/transcripts/2026-02-update.txt"><code>2026-02-update.txt</code></a> (if transcribed)</li>
        <li><strong>March 2026</strong> — corresponding deck and recording</li>
        <li><strong>April 2026</strong> — <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/engagement/OPDA all member update Apr 2026.pdf"><code>OPDA all member update Apr 2026.pdf</code></a></li>
        <li><strong>May 2026</strong> — <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/engagement/OPDA all member update May 2026.pdf"><code>OPDA all member update May 2026.pdf</code></a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="dpmsgSessions">DPMSG Trust &amp; Interoperability Steering Group</h2>
      <p>
        Five steering-group session transcripts on record (where transcription has been
        completed). Each session corresponds to one meeting date in the
        <a href="41-meetings-decisions.html">Meetings &amp; decisions</a> log.
      </p>
      <p>Location: <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/steering-group/transcripts/"><code>source/04-governance-bodies/steering-group/transcripts/</code></a></p>

      <h2 id="externalPresentations">External presentations &amp; demos</h2>
      <p>
        OPDA pitches, demos at industry events, partner conferences — each archived
        when a transcript or recording is available.
      </p>
      <p>Location: <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/05-engagement/presentations/"><code>source/05-engagement/presentations/</code></a></p>

      <h2 id="usage">Notes for downstream use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All transcripts are plain UTF-8 text. No timestamps in the YouTube auto-captions but speaker breaks usually appear as newlines.</li>
        <li>Where the canonical recording is on Vimeo (the SDC prize video), captions were captured manually from the player UI — slightly less complete than YouTube's auto-transcript.</li>
        <li>For corpus-level analysis, the JSON wrappers under <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=docs/data/resources/"><code>docs/data/resources/</code></a> only cover schema files; transcripts are not pre-bundled (they're small enough to fetch lazily).</li>
      </ul>

      <PageFooter
  prev={{ href: '43-video-library.html', label: 'Video library' }}
/>
</Layout>
